At 01:12 PM 1/30/2004 -0700, Jason Z Upper wrote:
>This problem you speak of -- is it particular to older T4 engines?  The 
>fan on my '78 engine is held on by 3 bolts with 1/2" (12.7mm) heads, and 
>is not held on by one big nut.  Since more than one of you has mentioned 
>the fan falling off, should I worry that mine might someday as well?

The three you're seeing are the ones that hold the fan to the hub.  The
"big one" the original poster had a problem with is the one that holds
the hub to the crank.

